# Environment Configuration for Vehicle Order Tracker

# =============================================================================
# AI EMAIL GENERATION CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================
# This application supports two methods for AI email generation:

# METHOD 1 (Recommended for Production): Server-Side Vertex AI Proxy
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Uses Google Cloud Vertex AI with Application Default Credentials (ADC).
# Requires:
# 1. A service account with "Vertex AI User" role attached to your Cloud Run service
# 2. No API keys exposed to the client
# 3. Server code in server/aiProxy.cjs handles the API calls
#
# Configuration (all optional, auto-detected in Cloud Run):
# GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT=your-project-id
# VERTEX_AI_LOCATION=us-central1
# PORT=8080

# METHOD 2 (Development/Fallback): Client-Side Gemini API
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Uses Gemini API directly from the browser with an API key.
# ⚠️  WARNING: API keys are visible in browser DevTools - use for development only!
#
# For local development:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Uncomment and set your Gemini API key below
# VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=your-api-key-here
#
# For Docker builds (pass as build argument):
# docker build --build-arg VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=your-key ...
#
# For Cloud Build (use substitutions in cloudbuild.yaml):
# _VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY: 'your-key'

# The application automatically detects which method is available:
# - If VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY is set: Uses client-side Gemini API
# - Otherwise: Falls back to server-side Vertex AI proxy

# =============================================================================
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT SETUP
# =============================================================================
# Option 1 (Recommended): Server-side with gcloud CLI
# Run: gcloud auth application-default login
# Then start both: npm run dev (client) and npm run server (API server)

# Option 2: Client-side with API key
# Create .env.local with:
# VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=your-gemini-api-key
# Then: npm run dev

# =============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# =============================================================================
# ⚠️  NEVER commit API keys to version control
# ⚠️  Client-side API keys are visible in browser - use server-side in production
# ⚠️  Use .env.local for local secrets (already in .gitignore)
# ✅  Production deployments should use Vertex AI with service account IAM roles
# ✅  Delete unused API keys from Google Cloud Console

